com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions.specialized.checked

Interface CheckedRunnable<T extends Throwable>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Throwable type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Runnable
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface CheckedRunnable<T extends Throwable>
extends Runnable
    Specialized Runnable that can throw any Throwable.
    See Also:
    CheckedSupplier, CheckedFn1

      • run

        default void run()
        Description copied from interface: java.lang.Runnable
        When an object implementing interface Runnable is used to create a thread, starting the thread causes the object's run method to be called in that separately executing thread.

        The general contract of the method run is that it may take any action whatsoever.
